{
  "texts": [
    "CMDs take second place in all applications but the Hate speech one, where they are outperformed by zero-shot classification.",
    "Depending on the dataset, RMDs can perform better or worse than some CMD variants, but they are always outperformed by the best-performing CMD.",
    "While the zero-shot approach relying on the more recent GPT-4 model outperforms RMDs and its predecessor (GPT-3.5-turbo) in most cases, its performance falls short of transformer models fine-tuned with manually coded data.",
    "Notably, GPT-4 performs worse than an extensively validated RMD on the Election data.",
    "While the performance of zeroshot classification can potentially be improved by adjusting the prompt or providing several examples (few-shot learning), this requires additional considerations regarding prompt design and example selection (Abdurahman et al., 2023; Chae & Davidson, 2023; Liu et al., 2021)."
  ]
}